<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-20T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="483" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety
                                Airways/101: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Port-of-Spain, Trinidad</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Demorest</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Port-of-Spain</hi>,] <hi rend="smallcaps">Trinidad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-20T16:00:00-04:00">August 20, 1929—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:04 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The French Consul has volunteered the information to me that the
                                French Government has offered the British Government airways
                                concessions <pb facs="0760" n="624" xml:id="pg_624"/> in French Indo
                                China or French Africa in exchange of similar concessions in British
                                West Indies to Compagnie Generale Aéropostale. The French Consul has
                                informed Governor of Trinidad of connection French company with
                                Tri-Motors Safety Airways, Incorporated, (New York, Rio, and Buenos
                                Aires Line).</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Demorest</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>